Log Management with SIEM Tools
Lab Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Install and configure the ELK Stack (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana) for centralized log management
Implement log parsing and normalization using Logstash filters
Create custom scripts for log analysis and threat detection
Configure log retention policies and rotation strategies
Build basic visualizations for security monitoring
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of system logs and their security importance
Familiarity with text editors (nano, vim)
Basic scripting knowledge (bash)
Understanding of networking fundamentals
