Troubleshooting Tips
Elasticsearch won't start:

Check Java installation: java -version
Verify memory: Elasticsearch needs minimum 2GB RAM
Check logs: sudo journalctl -u elasticsearch -f
Logstash not processing logs:

Verify configuration syntax: sudo /usr/share/logstash/bin/logstash --config.test_and_exit -f /etc/logstash/conf.d/siem-pipeline.conf
Check file permissions on log files
Review Logstash logs: sudo journalctl -u logstash -f
Kibana not accessible:

Verify Elasticsearch is running first
Check Kibana logs: sudo journalctl -u kibana -f
Ensure port 5601 is not blocked
No logs appearing in Elasticsearch:

Verify Logstash is reading log files
Check index exists: curl -X GET "localhost:9200/_cat/indices?v"
Generate test data and wait 1-2 minutes for processing
Conclusion
This lab introduced centralized log management using the ELK Stack as an open-source SIEM solution. Students learned to install and configure Elasticsearch, Logstash, and Kibana, create custom log analysis scripts, implement log retention policies, and build security monitoring dashboards. These skills are fundamental for security operations, incident response, and compliance monitoring in modern IT environments. The ELK Stack provides a scalable foundation for enterprise log management and security analytics.
